# Netflix Viewership Predictions

## Overview
This project focuses on analyzing Netflix viewership data to identify trends and build predictive models. The analysis aims to understand how historical viewership patterns can inform future audience behavior.

## Problem Statement
Streaming platforms rely heavily on predictive analytics to guide content strategy and user engagement. This project explores whether historical viewership data can be used to predict future trends and outcomes.

## Data Description
The dataset includes Netflix viewership metrics such as title performance, engagement indicators, and temporal attributes. Data cleaning and preprocessing were performed to prepare the dataset for analysis and modeling.

## Methods and Tools
- Python
- Data cleaning and exploratory analysis
- Feature engineering
- Predictive modeling techniques

## Results
The model identifies meaningful patterns in viewership behavior and demonstrates the feasibility of predicting trends using historical data. Results highlight the importance of feature selection and data quality in predictive performance.

## Key Takeaways
- Predictive modeling can uncover valuable insights in media consumption data
- Viewership trends are influenced by multiple interacting factors
- Data-driven approaches support strategic decision-making in streaming platforms
